{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Hi. I'm going to ask you to raise your arms and wave back,"},{"time":3000,"text":"just the way I am -- kind of a royal wave."},{"time":6000,"text":"You can mimic what you can see."},{"time":8000,"text":"You can program the hundreds of muscles in your arm."},{"time":11000,"text":"Soon, you'll be able to look inside your brain and program,"},{"time":16000,"text":"control the hundreds of brain areas that you see there."},{"time":18000,"text":"I'm going to tell you about that technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"People have wanted to look inside the human mind,"},{"time":22000,"text":"the human brain, for thousands of years."},{"time":25000,"text":"Well, coming out of the research labs just now, for our generation, is the possibility to do that."},{"time":30000,"text":"People envision this as being very difficult."},{"time":32000,"text":"You had to take a spaceship, shrink it down, inject it into the bloodstream."},{"time":36000,"text":"It was terribly dangerous. (Laughter)"},{"time":38000,"text":"You could be attacked by white blood cells in the arteries."},{"time":41000,"text":"But now, we have a real technology to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"We're going to fly into my colleague Peter's brain."},{"time":47000,"text":"We're going to do it non-invasively using MRI."},{"time":50000,"text":"We don't have to inject anything. We don't need radiation."},{"time":54000,"text":"We will be able to fly into the anatomy of Peter's brain -- literally, fly into his body --"},{"time":59000,"text":"but more importantly, we can look into his mind."},{"time":61000,"text":"When Peter moves his arm, that yellow spot you see there"},{"time":64000,"text":"is the interface to the functioning of Peter's mind taking place."},{"time":68000,"text":"Now you've seen before that with electrodes you can control robotic arms,"},{"time":71000,"text":"that brain imaging and scanners can show you the insides of brains."},{"time":75000,"text":"What's new is that that process has typically taken days or months of analysis."},{"time":80000,"text":"We've collapsed that through technology to milliseconds,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and that allows us to let Peter to look at his brain in real time as he's inside the scanner."},{"time":87000,"text":"He can look at these 65,000 points of activation per second."},{"time":92000,"text":"If he can see this pattern in his own brain, he can learn how to control it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"There have been three ways to try to impact the brain:"},{"time":99000,"text":"the therapist's couch, pills and the knife."},{"time":103000,"text":"This is a fourth alternative that you are soon going to have."},{"time":107000,"text":"We all know that as we form thoughts, they form deep channels in our minds and in our brains."},{"time":112000,"text":"Chronic pain is an example. If you burn yourself, you pull your hand away."},{"time":116000,"text":"But if you're still in pain in six months' or six years' time,"},{"time":120000,"text":"it's because these circuits are producing pain that's no longer helping you."},{"time":124000,"text":"If we can look at the activation in the brain that's producing the pain,"},{"time":127000,"text":"we can form 3D models and watch in real time the brain process information,"},{"time":132000,"text":"and then we can select the areas that produce the pain."},{"time":135000,"text":"So put your arms back up and flex your bicep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"Now imagine that you will soon be able to look inside your brain"},{"time":142000,"text":"and select brain areas to do that same thing."},{"time":144000,"text":"What you're seeing here is, we've selected the pathways in the brain of a chronic pain patient."},{"time":148000,"text":"This may shock you, but we're literally reading this person's brain in real time."},{"time":152000,"text":"They're watching their own brain activation,"},{"time":154000,"text":"and they're controlling the pathway that produces their pain."},{"time":158000,"text":"They're learning to flex this system that releases their own endogenous opiates."},{"time":162000,"text":"As they do it, in the upper left is a display"},{"time":165000,"text":"that's yoked to their brain activation of their own pain being controlled."},{"time":169000,"text":"When they control their brain, they can control their pain."},{"time":173000,"text":"This is an investigational technology,"},{"time":175000,"text":"but, in clinical trials, we're seeing a 44 to 64 percent decrease in chronic pain patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180000,"text":"This is not \"The Matrix.\" You can only do this to yourself. You take control."},{"time":185000,"text":"I've seen inside my brain. You will too, soon."},{"time":189000,"text":"When you do, what do you want to control?"},{"time":192000,"text":"You will be able to look at all the aspects that make you yourself, all your experiences."},{"time":197000,"text":"These are some of the areas we're working on today that I don't have time to go into in detail."},{"time":202000,"text":"But I want to leave with you the big question."},{"time":205000,"text":"We are the first generation that's going to be able to enter into,"},{"time":208000,"text":"using this technology, the human mind and brain."},{"time":211000,"text":"Where will we take it?"}]}]}